#Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Letshego Zulu is turning tragedy into triumph. The adventurer lost her husband Gugu Zulu on Mount Kilimanjaro nearly three years ago. She's now written a book, charting that fateful journey. READ: Remembering Gugu Zulu It's a story about death. But in many ways, it's a celebration of life. She says the book is more about helping people face various challenges in life. "You know, whether it's losing a job. Losing a house. Losing a loved one."